      <p>A friend of mine sent out postcards after so many months of being married (6? 9?). On the front was a funny picture of them. On the back, a pre-printed message about how lame they were not getting their thank-you notes out, but how much they appreciated us being at their wedding and our thoughtful gifts, etc. and that thank you notes woud come eventually.  </></>Since the picture &#038; letter reflected their personality, it was actually better than the standard &#8220;Thanks for the gift, it was great&#8221; note.</p>
