  <li id="comment-11264" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/04225535216850178185" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Emily</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/04/because-of-the-cookies/#comment-11264"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-05-27T18:30:00-04:00">Tuesday, May 27, 2008 at 6:30 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thanks for pointing out this lovely recipe to everyone, Molly!  I had planned to make them the past two weekends, but have been swamped with work.  Luckily, I have a great boyfriend who decided to finally try his hand at baking and made them late last night!  Well&#8230;he actually got bored halfway through and I finished them, but it&#8217;s the thought that counts, right?</>To the readers having problems with their cookies flattening out, my guess is that it&#8217;s the size.  My cookies that were half a Tbs in size ended up like over-sized button cookies, while anything a bit bigger tended to flatten out.  Equally delicious, but not quite as aesthetically pleasing.  Hope this helps some!</p>
    </div>

